---
description: Quality gate before finishing Flutter feature changes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Change Quality Gate

Before finalizing any implementation:

- Run targeted analyzer/lint checks for changed files.
- Ensure no unresolved imports or missing registrations.
- Confirm new providers/controllers are actually used by views/routes.
- Avoid dead code and unused variables introduced by refactor.
- Keep changes scoped to user request; avoid opportunistic broad rewrites.
- Preserve existing UX patterns unless user requested UI behavior changes.

# Response Quality

- Explain what changed, where, and why in concise project-specific language.
- Call out assumptions or backend contract dependencies when relevant.
